description:
&lt;p&gt;We have a rare opportunity to a recruit a Band 7 acute Occupational Therapy Team leader within Acute Frailty team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Currently the post is 30 hours per week, however, for the right candidate we are not necessarily fixed to these specific hours and have the opportunity be creative to meet the demands of the service…&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So if you are interested and have the skills we are looking for to join our supportive and forward thinking dynamic team, but the advertised hours don’t work for you, then please do not hesitate to contact the OT Manager Lorna Courtney 01234 792120 to discuss possible options, you just never know, you may have missed out on your perfect job because you didn’t ask..&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be leading the team servicing Acute Frailty wards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You and your team will be providing care to a diverse community on the acute Frailty wards, providing quality OT assessments and OT recommendations of function based on individual needs. Including provision of early assessment in order to facilitate a safe discharge Signposting onto other agencies liaising with families.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Using your coaching and counselling skills to negotiate ways of engagement for patients who are reluctant.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be leading a team of approx. seven OT’s and technicians.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be providing a quality educational environment for OT students and supervising junior staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be using the structure KSF and probation competency pack in order to ensure all staff are providing safe and efficient ways of working.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have specialist knowledge in Frailty and have experience with working with Patients with dementia and supporting the teams to appreciate the approaches available to assist therapies with this client group. This area of work is now at the forefront of acute care looking to implement initiatives such as a Frailty unit and working with the CGA’s (comprehensive geriatrician Assessments) and the Occupational therapy Team leader will play a part in developing the Frailty pathways&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Lorna Courtney Job title:Occupational Therapy manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: lorna.courtney@bedfordhospital.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 01234 355122 ext 2037&lt;/p&gt;
